  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voluntary Contribution of 2 Million Euros to IOM for the Humanitarian Response to the Crisis in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2021, more than 1,260,000 undocumented Afghans have returned to Afghanistan from Pakistan and the Islamic Republic of Iran &#x2014; the highest return total of any year on record. Combined with 2020 returns of over 865,000 persons, over 2 million undocumented Afghans have crossed back into Afghanistan. Afghanistan has well exceeded the Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP) estimate of 654,000 total returns in 2021 and the record high return of 2020, with additional surges expected in return linked to many undocumented Afghans leaving the country through irregular means or overstaying Iranian visas. To address the glaring gap in available humanitarian support for this caseload and for high numbers that are expected in 2022, IOM continues to deliver lifesaving assistance to the most vulnerable, undocumented returnees from the Islamic Republic of Iran and Pakistan.</narrative>
  </description>
